cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.LG

This paper deals with image enhancement, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of contour trees to extract a hierarchical representation of the topology of an image suggests that this paper may also fall under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or graphics (cs.GR). The paper proposes topology-aware transfer functions, which may involve machine learning techniques (cs.LG) or data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the evaluation of the approach with grayscale and color images suggests that this paper may also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
